    {
      "id": "stage-01",
      "order": 1,
      "title": "Clasificación de triángulos",
      "html": "<!doctype html>\n<html lang=\"es\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"utf-8\" />\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width,initial-scale=1\" />\n  <title>Clasificación de triángulos</title>\n  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/katex@0.16.11/dist/katex.min.css\">\n  <script defer src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/katex@0.16.11/dist/katex.min.js\"></script>\n  <script defer src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/katex@0.16.11/dist/contrib/auto-render.min.js\"></script>\n  <style>\n    body { font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, Segoe UI, Roboto, sans-serif; line-height: 1.5; padding: 1rem; }\n    h1, h2, h3 { margin: 0.2em 0; }\n    .badge { display:inline-block; font-size: 0.8rem; padding: 0.15rem 0.5rem; border-radius: 999px; background:#eef; margin-right: .4rem; }\n    .example, .task { border: 1px solid #ddd; border-radius: 8px; padding: 0.8rem; margin: 0.8rem 0; }\n    .note { font-size: .9rem; color:#333; background:#fafafa; padding:.6rem .8rem; border-left: 3px solid #ddd; border-radius:6px; }\n    .tip { background: #f0fbff; border-left: 4px solid #6ac8ff; padding: 10px 12px; margin: 14px 0; }\n    .grid { display:grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px,1fr)); gap: 14px; }\n    .card { border: 1px solid #e5e7eb; border-radius: 10px; padding: 12px; text-align:center; }\n    .card .label { font-weight: 700; color: #4338ca; margin: 0.3rem 0 0; }\n    .card .desc { font-size: 0.85rem; color: #555; margin: 0.2rem 0; }\n    svg { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display:block; margin: 8px auto; }\n    .step { margin:.3rem 0; }\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <h1>Clasificación de triángulos</h1>\n  <p><span class=\"badge\">5.º grado</span><span class=\"badge\">Geometría</span></p>\n\n  <div class=\"note\">\n    <strong>Objetivo de aprendizaje (Guía del Docente, Ecuador):</strong> Reconocer, comparar y clasificar paralelogramos, trapecios y triángulos como conceptos matemáticos y en los objetos del entorno.\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"tip\">\n    <strong>Propiedad fundamental:</strong> La suma de los ángulos interiores de cualquier triángulo es siempre $180°$.\n    $$\\alpha + \\beta + \\gamma = 180°$$\n  </div>\n\n  <h2>Según sus lados</h2>\n  <div class=\"grid\">\n    <!-- Equilátero -->\n    <div class=\"card\">\n      <svg viewBox=\"0 0 140 130\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"130\" height=\"120\">\n        <polygon points=\"70,10 10,115 130,115\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#e11d48\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" />\n        <text x=\"30\" y=\"72\" font-size=\"10\" fill=\"#555\" transform=\"rotate(-60,30,72)\">a</text>\n        <text x=\"105\" y=\"72\" font-size=\"10\" fill=\"#555\" transform=\"rotate(60,105,72)\">a</text>\n        <text x=\"65\" y=\"128\" font-size=\"10\" fill=\"#555\">a</text>\n      </svg>\n      <p class=\"label\">Equilátero</p>\n      <p class=\"desc\">3 lados iguales<br/>3 ángulos de $60°$</p>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Isósceles -->\n    <div class=\"card\">\n      <svg viewBox=\"0 0 140 130\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"130\" height=\"120\">\n        <polygon points=\"70,10 20,115 120,115\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#7c3aed\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" />\n        <text x=\"36\" y=\"68\" font-size=\"10\" fill=\"#555\" transform=\"rotate(-65,36,68)\">a</text>\n        <text x=\"102\" y=\"68\" font-size=\"10\" fill=\"#555\" transform=\"rotate(65,102,68)\">a</text>\n        <text x=\"65\" y=\"128\" font-size=\"10\" fill=\"#555\">b</text>\n      </svg>\n      <p class=\"label\">Isósceles</p>\n      <p class=\"desc\">2 lados iguales<br/>2 ángulos iguales</p>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Escaleno -->\n    <div class=\"card\">\n      <svg viewBox=\"0 0 150 130\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"140\" height=\"120\">\n        <polygon points=\"50,10 10,115 140,115\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#0891b2\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" />\n        <text x=\"22\" y=\"68\" font-size=\"10\" fill=\"#555\" transform=\"rotate(-69,22,68)\">a</text>\n        <text x=\"100\" y=\"68\" font-size=\"10\" fill=\"#555\" transform=\"rotate(37,100,68)\">b</text>\n        <text x=\"70\" y=\"128\" font-size=\"10\" fill=\"#555\">c</text>\n      </svg>\n      <p class=\"label\">Escaleno</p>\n      <p class=\"desc\">3 lados diferentes<br/>3 ángulos diferentes</p>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <h2>Según sus ángulos</h2>\n  <div class=\"grid\">\n    <!-- Acutángulo -->\n    <div class=\"card\">\n      <svg viewBox=\"0 0 140 120\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"130\" height=\"110\">\n        <polygon points=\"70,10 15,110 125,110\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#16a34a\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" />\n        <path d=\"M 30,110 A 15,15 0 0,0 25,98\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#e11d48\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" />\n        <path d=\"M 110,110 A 15,15 0 0,1 115,98\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#e11d48\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" />\n        <path d=\"M 62,24 A 15,15 0 0,1 78,24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#e11d48\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" />\n      </svg>\n      <p class=\"label\">Acutángulo</p>\n      <p class=\"desc\">Todos los ángulos son agudos (menores de $90°$)</p>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Rectángulo -->\n    <div class=\"card\">\n      <svg viewBox=\"0 0 140 120\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"130\" height=\"110\">\n        <polygon points=\"15,110 15,20 125,110\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#f97316\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" />\n        <rect x=\"15\" y=\"95\" width=\"15\" height=\"15\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#e11d48\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" />\n      </svg>\n      <p class=\"label\">Rectángulo</p>\n      <p class=\"desc\">Tiene un ángulo recto ($90°$)</p>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Obtusángulo -->\n    <div class=\"card\">\n      <svg viewBox=\"0 0 160 120\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"150\" height=\"110\">\n        <polygon points=\"80,15 5,110 155,110\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#dc2626\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" />\n        <path d=\"M 20,110 A 18,18 0 0,0 14,95\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#16a34a\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" />\n        <path d=\"M 140,110 A 18,18 0 0,1 146,95\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#16a34a\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" />\n        <path d=\"M 70,29 A 18,18 0 0,1 90,29\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#e11d48\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" />\n      </svg>\n      <p class=\"label\">Obtusángulo</p>\n      <p class=\"desc\">Tiene un ángulo obtuso (mayor de $90°$)</p>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"example\">\n    <h4>Ejemplo</h4>\n    <p>Un triángulo tiene ángulos de $50°$ y $70°$. ¿Cuánto mide el tercer ángulo?</p>\n    <p class=\"step\">$\\gamma = 180° - 50° - 70° = 60°$</p>\n    <p>Como todos los ángulos son menores de $90°$, es un triángulo <strong>acutángulo</strong>.</p>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"note\">\n    <strong>Recuerda:</strong> Un triángulo puede clasificarse por sus lados <strong>y</strong> por sus ángulos al mismo tiempo. Por ejemplo: «triángulo isósceles rectángulo».\n  </div>\n\n  <script>\n  document.addEventListener(\"DOMContentLoaded\", function() {\n    renderMathInElement(document.body, {\n      delimiters: [{left: \"$$\", right: \"$$\", display: true},{left: \"$\", right: \"$\", display: false}]\n    });\n  });\n  </script>\n</body>\n</html>",
      "formulas": [
        "\\alpha + \\beta + \\gamma = 180°"
      ],
